SELECT 'b1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','Carissa','Fenceroy','carissa-fenceroy','LMSW','she, her, hers','Welcome! My name is Carissa (she, her, hers). I have had the great honor of working with children, families, and individuals of all ages and backgrounds in various capacities throughout my career. My experience includes working in the child welfare system, supporting parents in developing parenting and self-sufficiency skills to help reunify their families. I have also worked as a home visitor, guiding pregnant and parenting teenagers as they strive to reach their goals for success. Additionally, my role as a school social worker allowed me to teach elementary children conflict resolution and emotional regulation skills in both individual and group settings.

With eight years of experience in social work, I have developed strong skills in supporting individuals facing multiple sources of stress and helping them create solution-focused plans to navigate life’s challenges. My approach to therapeutic services is client-centered, empowering individuals to take the lead in their mental health journey. I naturally adopt a strengths-based and solution-focused perspective, always working to validate and affirm the unique experiences of those I serve. I also practice from a systems and environmental lens, recognizing how relationships, culture, and broader societal factors can impact well-being.

During our time together, you can always expect a warm and welcoming environment. I will encourage you to share your story, explore your hopes for the future, and work alongside you in identifying and achieving your goals. My role is to support you in managing stress, building healthy relationships, and creating meaningful change in your life.Although I am currently an intern, my extensive background in social work, combined with my ongoing training to become a therapist, allows me to provide skilled and compassionate care. You can feel confident knowing that I bring both experience and dedication to helping you on your journey.','/images/team/carissa-fenceroy.jpg','https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1724627','c3c376ab-3ea5-48c1-be6e-a72964a2e144','HYBRID','ACCEPTING',TRUE,90,now(),now()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM therapists WHERE tenant_id='a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001' AND slug='carissa-fenceroy');

SELECT 'b1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002','a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','Maggie','Reichler','maggie-reichler',NULL,NULL,'Hello! My name is Maggie, and I’m currently completing my Master’s in Clinical Mental Health Counseling at Arizona State University. My hobbies are painting, hiking, meditating, traveling, going to the gym, getting tattoos, and hanging with family, friends, and dogs. I am deeply passionate about helping people heal and grow in a warm, authentic, and collaborative environment.

Through our work together, I’ll help you see life in a new light and connect with yourself on a deeper level. My approach is integrative and personalized to your unique needs. I draw from holistic and mindfulness-based practices to help you live more fully in the present, and Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT) to help you navigate struggles while building a fulfilling life in line with your values. I also use Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) to help you reframe unhelpful thought processes and be more aware of how your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors affect each other. My work is trauma-informed and guided by strengths-based, person-centered perspectives that respect and celebrate your individuality, autonomy, and values. I see you as a whole person, and our work will honor every part of your experiences and who you are.

I have experience working with people of all ages from all backgrounds; come as you are! Together, we can explore what brings you here, whether that’s anxiety, depression, trauma, self-worth, relationship and family struggles, or identity. No matter where you are in your journey, I strive to help you feel safe, understood, cared for, and empowered toward meaningful growth.

Therapy is an experience like no other, and I am committed to making it a place where you can fully embrace who you are in a non-judgmental, compassionate space. Taking this step to seek help is an act of courage and self-compassion. You are not alone, you’re cared for and supported every step of the way. I’m so excited to meet you, and I’d be honored to be beside you through your journey!

Ages:
Adults (18+)
Adolescents (14-17)','/images/team/maggie-reichler.jpg','https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1960700','0fb268c9-100d-4c24-b8b6-fafcbe777e72','HYBRID','ACCEPTING',TRUE,91,now(),now()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM therapists WHERE tenant_id='a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001' AND slug='maggie-reichler');

SELECT 'b1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000003','a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','Sukhmani','Khalsa','sukhmani-khalsa',NULL,NULL,'Welcome! My name is Sukhmani and I am excited and honored to be a part of your journey!

I am currently pursuing a Master of Social Work at ASU. My professional journey began as a case manager at an Arizona homeless shelter and most recently I was an intern in the clinical therapy department at Calvary Healing Center, one of Arizona’s premier residential treatment programs for substance use disorders. There, I worked with individuals navigating addiction, anxiety, trauma, and major life transitions. I supported clients by helping them develop coping skills, increase emotional regulation, clarify their values and goals, and build motivation for lasting change.

I believe healing and self-clarity happen when an individual feels safe, understood, and respected; especially during times when life feels overwhelming or out of control. My approach to therapy is warm, compassionate, collaborative, and grounded in the belief that every person already carries strengths that can be built upon, even when they don’t feel accessible.

My work is trauma-informed, strengths-based, and influenced by Dialectical Behavior Therapy (DBT). In our time together, I want to help you strengthen self-awareness and self-compassion. We then can develop practical tools for managing intense emotions, reducing anxiety, and improving distress tolerance. I strive to meet clients where they are, without judgment, and to create a space where vulnerability feels safe.

In our work together, I aim to be a steady, supportive presence while helping you reconnect with your strengths, and move towards your goals and the life you want to create.','/images/team/sukhmani-khalsa.jpg','https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1960711','20e3a720-5619-4bc8-9f52-45b3dc09cbe9','HYBRID','ACCEPTING',TRUE,92,now(),now()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM therapists WHERE tenant_id='a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001' AND slug='sukhmani-khalsa');

SELECT 'b1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000004','a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','Kira','McSherry','kira-mcsherry',NULL,NULL,'Hi, I’m Kira, an intern therapist at Brazen Therapy, lifelong learner, mom, wife, and proud cat lover. I believe therapy should feel like a place where you can exhale, feel safe being yourself, and begin making sense of what you’re carrying.

I’m currently completing my Master of Counseling at Arizona State University and also hold a Bachelor of Science in Human and Family Development. My background shapes how I see people, not as problems to be fixed, but as whole humans shaped by relationships, attachment, and the stories they’ve lived.

My approach is trauma-informed, relational, and attachment-based, with a focus on how early experiences, family dynamics, and life transitions influence how we feel, connect, and cope. I’m especially interested in supporting people navigating:

* Self-worth, identity, and belonging
* Fear of abandonment or rejection
* Adoption and the adoption triad
* ADHD and neurodivergence
* Grief, loss, and major life transitions
* Relationship and attachment concerns

I’m open to working with children, teens, adolescents, adults, individuals, and couples, and I enjoy supporting people across different stages of life as they navigate relationships, emotions, and change.

As an adoptee, I bring both professional training and lived experience into the room. I understand how experiences of attachment, loss, and belonging can shape how we see ourselves and relate to others. My goal is to create a space that feels validating, grounded, and genuinely human.

In sessions, I show up with curiosity, warmth, and collaboration. I believe you are the expert on your own life, and therapy works best when we explore things together, at your pace, in a way that feels safe and respectful.

Outside the therapy room, I’m married and a mom, and I know firsthand how layered and complex family life can be. I enjoy reading, staying active, cheering on the Phoenix Suns and ASU Sun Devils, and spending time with my cats, who are very good at reminding me to slow down and be present.

Whether you’re feeling stuck, overwhelmed, disconnected, or simply ready for something to shift, you don’t have to do it alone. I’d be honored to walk alongside you.','/images/team/kira-mcsherry.jpg','https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1960704','08c21cf1-dea6-4d45-b5b1-215481d1eb77','HYBRID','ACCEPTING',TRUE,93,now(),now()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM therapists WHERE tenant_id='a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001' AND slug='kira-mcsherry');

SELECT 'b1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000005','a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','Robin','Burnam','robin-burnam',NULL,NULL,'Hello, my name is Robin Burnam, and I am a Master of Social Work intern from Arizona State University. I am originally from Ohio (Go Bucks!) and relocated to Arizona four years ago. I bring over 20 years of experience supporting teenagers and young adults on college and university campuses, where I have worked with individuals navigating a wide range of academic, personal, and emotional challenges. In my personal time, I enjoy outdoor activities with my family and supporting the arts at concerts, galleries, and live theatre performances.

My clinical interests include supporting adolescents and adults experiencing anxiety, depression, life transitions, identity exploration, grief, and relationship concerns. I understand that life can be unpredictable and confusing at times, and believe that each person is the expert in their own life. Finding someone with the right skill set to support you and who provides a space where you feel safe and accepted is the most important part of the therapeutic process.

I take a compassionate, client-centered, and strengths-based approach to therapy, working collaboratively with clients to create a safe, inclusive, and welcoming space for healing and growth. My work is grounded in trauma-informed care and incorporates solution-focused interventions, mindfulness techniques, and motivational interviewing to support clients in identifying their strengths, building resilience, and working toward client-focused goals.

I am committed to honoring each client’s lived experience and supporting individuals of all ages and backgrounds with respect, empathy, and cultural humility. I am currently completing my MSW degree and provide clinical services under the supervision of a licensed clinical social worker.','/images/team/robin-burnam.jpg','https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1960713','e35c2933-d160-455e-884a-321893358e66','HYBRID','ACCEPTING',TRUE,94,now(),now()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM therapists WHERE tenant_id='a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001' AND slug='robin-burnam');

SELECT 'b1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000006','a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001','Mimi','Jiang','mimi-jiang',NULL,NULL,'Hi, my name is Mimi. Welcome in! I am a counselor-in-training completing my Master of Counseling degree at Arizona State University. I support individuals who may be navigating anxiety, depression, trauma, relationship concerns, identity exploration, cultural adjustment, and life transition-related stress. As a practitioner with cross-cultural experiences and identities, I am deeply interested in how cultures and society shape the ways we understand ourselves and the world around us. I am especially passionate about working with individuals who hold intersecting identities, including relational, racial and cultural, gender and sexual identities. This includes young adults, college and international students, and LGBTQ+ clients.

I provide counseling in English and Mandarin Chinese. My approach is integrative, trauma-informed, and strengths-based. In our sessions, we may work on understanding the difficult emotions you have been carrying, identifying and challenging unhelpful thought patterns, building practical coping skills, and exploring relationship patterns and their impacts. I draw from person-centered therapy, cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT), and acceptance and commitment therapy (ACT) to support clients in ways that fit their needs and goals. Together, we will work toward helping you feel more grounded, connected, and empowered in your daily life.

I believe therapy is a collaborative process built on trust, respect, and curiosity. As a counselor-in-training, I value lifelong learning, cultural humility, and openness. My hope is to create an affirming, nonjudgmental, and supportive space where you can feel heard, accepted, and empowered to explore who you are, where you are now, and who you are becoming.

Outside of counseling, I enjoy playing mobile games, listening to pop music, singing, and playing guitar. I bring warmth, joy, and a sense of humor into my relationships. I look forward to getting to know you and supporting you as we work together.

Populations:

Individuals
Teens (14+)

Adults (18+)','/images/team/mimi-jiang.jpg','https://spwidget-brazentherapy.clientsecure.me/widget/service?appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&channel=client_portal&clinicianId=2051007','98b84dcd-0fb1-4968-a035-7ba36d5c7157','HYBRID','ACCEPTING',TRUE,95,now(),now()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM therapists WHERE tenant_id='a0000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001' AND slug='mimi-jiang');

